comments: Kuzma (WAS) rests his forearm on Brunson's (NYK) side and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Poole (WAS) lowers his arm down toward the ball and marginal brush contact occurs with DiVincenzo's (NYK) arm during his layup attempt at the basket,
Anunoby (NYK) holds his forearm out as Poole (WAS) steps toward the offensive player and marginal contact occurs prior to the start of the drive.
Avdija (WAS) rests his hand on Brunson's (NYK) shoulder and removes the marginal contact as Brunson starts his drive.
Avdija (WAS) holds his arm out and contact occurs with Brunson's (NYK) arms after his gather, which affects his SQBR prior to the pass.
Anunoby (NYK) aligns along Avdija's (WAS) path after his gather and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Avdija (WAS) moves alongside Brunson's (NYK) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the drive.
Avdija (WAS) brings his hands toward Anunoby (NYK) and marginal contact occurs as Avdija releases away to roll.
DiVincenzo (NYK) extends his arm out and contact occurs with Poole's (WAS) side, which affects his upward shooting motion.
Brunson (NYK) and Avdija (WAS) engage during the inbound and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.

Replay review of the foul called on Poole (WAS) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Poole makes clean contact with the ball and legally deflects it away from Randle (NYK) during his dribble. After the deflection, Randle grabs and holds Poole's arm, which restricts Poole's pursuit of the loose ball. A loose ball foul is correctly attributed to Randle and Poole is awarded two free throws as Washington is in the bonus penalty.
Avdija (WAS) is drawn into the air towards Brunson (NYK) but the contact is marginal.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Brunson (NYK) makes last contact with the ball before it bounces out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Washington.
Avdija (WAS) commits a take foul on Randle (NYK).
Kuzma (WAS) establishes himself in the frontcourt prior to coming into contact with the ball.
Anunoby (NYK) rests his hand on Kuzma's (WAS) side as both players launch into the air and the contact during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Bagley III (WAS) places and removes his hand from Randle's (NYK) upper back and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Avdija (WAS) commits a take foul on Anunoby (NYK).
Bagley III (WAS) firms up in Hartenstein's (NYK) path and does not deliver any illegal contact when setting the pick.
Jones (WAS) and Brunson (NYK) engage and disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Shamet (WAS) commits a take foul on DiVincenzo (NYK).
